Illustration with substitution model

The first one
(+ 4 5)
  (if (= 4 0) 5 (inc (+ (dec 4) 5))))
inc (+ 3 5)
inc (if (= 3 0) 5 (inc (+ (dec 3) 5))))
inc inc (+ 2 5)
inc inc (if (= 2 0) 5 (inc (+ (dec 2) 5))))
inc inc inc (+ 1 5)
inc inc inc (if (= 1 0) 5 (inc (+ (dec 1) 5))))
inc inc inc inc (+ 0 5)
inc inc inc inc (if (= 0 0) 5 (inc (+ (dec 0) 5))))
inc inc inc inc 5
result = 9

The first one is recursive.

The second one
(+ 4 5)
  (if (= 4 0) 5 (+ (dec 4) (inc 5))))
（+ 3 6）
  (if (= 3 0) 5 (+ (dec 3) (inc 6))))
（+ 2 7）
  (if (= 2 0) 5 (+ (dec 2) (inc 7))))
（+ 1 8）
（+ 0 9）
result = 9

The second one is iterative, because the result of the previous application is applied to the procedure repeatedly.
